According to Achim (p.167-170, 179, 182-183, 185) and Deletant (p.189-190), the measures reflected Antonescu's views on &quot;social problems&quot; more than a racist perspective. However, Kelso (p.99-100) believes the report was a notable factor in the decision to deport the Romani people.
